# GitLab Runner on Kubernetes Setup Guide

**TTM Technologies — Hillsborough RKE2 Cluster**  
**Date:** April 2026  
**Author:** Alhaji Suma

-----

## Overview

This document covers the deployment of a GitLab Runner on the Hillsborough RKE2 Kubernetes cluster, registered against the existing GitLab instance at `gitlab.ttmtech.com`. The runner enables CI/CD pipelines to execute on the Hillsborough cluster.

-----

## Architecture

```
gitlab.ttmtech.com          ← existing GitLab (unchanged)
    ↓ dispatches jobs
Hillsborough K8s cluster    ← runner manager pod polls for jobs
    ↓ spawns ephemeral pods
Job pods execute pipelines  ← images from internal registry
    ↓ reports results back
gitlab.ttmtech.com          ← job succeeded/failed
```

### Key Facts

|Property         |Value                                                                      |
|-----------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|GitLab Instance  |gitlab.ttmtech.com                                                         |
|Runner Namespace |gitlab-runner                                                              |
|Concurrent Jobs  |4                                                                          |
|Executor         |Kubernetes                                                                 |
|Internal Registry|img-registry.ttmtech.local:5000                                            |
|Default Job Image|img-registry.ttmtech.local:5000/gitlab/gitlab-base:v18.10.3                |
|Helper Image     |img-registry.ttmtech.local:5000/gitlab/gitlab-runner-helper:x86_64-v18.10.1|

