## Step 3 — Deploy Runner

### 3.1 Runner Values (gitlab-runner-values.yaml)

```yaml
gitlabUrl: https://gitlab.ttmtech.com
runnerToken: "<token-from-step-1>"

concurrent: 4

rbac:
  create: true
  serviceAccount:
    create: true

image:
  registry: img-registry.ttmtech.local:5000
  image: gitlab/gitlab-runner
  tag: latest

securityContext:
  allowPrivilegeEscalation: true
  runAsNonRoot: false
  runAsUser: 0
  privileged: true

podSecurityContext:
  runAsNonRoot: false
  runAsUser: 0
  fsGroup: 0

certsSecretName: gitlab-ttmtech-ca

runners:
  config: |
    [[runners]]
      tls-ca-file = "/home/gitlab-runner/.gitlab-runner/certs/gitlab.ttmtech.com.crt"
      [runners.kubernetes]
        namespace = "gitlab-runner"
        image = "img-registry.ttmtech.local:5000/gitlab/gitlab-base:v18.10.3"
        helper_image = "img-registry.ttmtech.local:5000/gitlab/gitlab-runner-helper:x86_64-v18.10.1"
        pull_policy = "if-not-present"
        cpu_request = "500m"
        cpu_limit = "2"
        memory_request = "512Mi"
        memory_limit = "4Gi"
```

### 3.2 Deploy

```bash
helm upgrade --install gitlab-runner gitlab/gitlab-runner \
  -n gitlab-runner \
  -f ~/gitlab-runner-values.yaml
```

### 3.3 Verify

```bash
# Check pod is running
kubectl get pods -n gitlab-runner

# Check logs - should show "Runner registered successfully"
kubectl logs -n gitlab-runner -l app=gitlab-runner
```

Expected output:

```
Verifying runner... is alive
Runner registered successfully
Configuration loaded  builds=0 max_builds=4
```

