## Troubleshooting

### Check Runner Status

```bash
# Pod status
kubectl get pods -n gitlab-runner

# Logs
kubectl logs -n gitlab-runner -l app=gitlab-runner -f

# Watch job pods during pipeline
kubectl get pods -n gitlab-runner -w
```

### Common Issues

|Issue                                          |Resolution                                                                       |
|-----------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|`x509: certificate signed by unknown authority`|Verify `gitlab-ttmtech-ca` secret exists and `certsSecretName` is set in values  |
|`403 Forbidden`                                |Runner token is project/group type not instance type — recreate via rails console|
|`ImagePullBackOff`                             |Image not in internal registry — pull and push from internet-connected machine   |
|Runner pod restarting                          |Check security context — `runAsUser: 0` and `privileged: true` required          |
|Jobs not picked up                             |Verify runner shows as online in gitlab.ttmtech.com Admin Area → CI/CD → Runners |

